    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A group of shell marbles, the name deriving from 'lumaca,' the Italian word for snail. There are both ancient and modern varieties; the best known modern lumachella comes from Tirol in Austria and is dark gray-brown with shells retaining their pearly lining.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
